{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1440017194,"nonce":"5PBhDsDVw20yg9+DOKWQ+69f8g0=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMDE5OTUxNDQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/252","origin":"github"},"title":"bedtools bamtobed with -bedpe option should not require name sorted bam files","message":"Currently, using the bedtools bamtobed tool on paired end data and specifying the bedpe option requires the user to supply a name sorted bam file. In Galaxy, this is not really doable since Galaxy requires BAM files to be sorted by chromosome location (see: galaxyproject/tools-devteam#210).\n\nI would suggest implementing the sort within the tool and piping the result to bedtools. This eliminates the headache for the user and doesn't generate a useless (and large) sorted  BAM file. See https://github.com/lparsons/galaxy_tools/tree/master/tools/htseq_count for one example of this.","files":null}]}